description:
One shot telling the story where Iron Man dies instead of Captain America.

The book goes through the five stages of grief just like the Fallen Son series already had, only quicker (to fit it all in one book). The stages are about a page or two each. The ending of the story has Iron Man's casket floating in outer space with the Skrull invasion (which happened to end the Civil War in the normal story arc) heading towards Earth in the background. The Watcher sees the inevitable doom of the green planet without the help of the, now dead, Iron Man and says, "It wasn't supposed to be this way..."

Also featuring part 2 of What If the Runaways became the Young Avengers? Part 3 continues next week in What If? Fantastic Four.
name: What If? Fallen Son

description:
The Back To The Future comics are based upon the characters seen in the cult hit movie series, Back To The Future. Both the films and the comic book series sees young Marty McFly and Dr Emmett Brown traveling through time sharing bizarre and exciting adventures along the way.

Dr Emmett Brown is the one responsible for the creation of the time machine, he spent many years planning out and developing the Flux Capacitor, which is what makes time travel possible.

However, in order for Marty or the Doc to time travel, they need to reach a speed of 88 miles per hour crossed with a nuclear reaction. So Dr Emmett Brown used a modified DeLorean as his time vehicle, which is the main piece of equipment used in their stories.

Many of the stories revolve around the time vehicle, and it creates much of the drama. For example, the first time Marty McFly traveled back to 1955, he had no plutonium to bring him back home again. Or again, in the old west when the fuel tank was pierced, and he therefore couldn't move the vehicle up to a speed of 88 miles per hour.

The comics are a little less techincal than the films are, but are still based on the same premise.
name: Back to the Future

description:
Cosmic Powers Unlimited was part of Marvel's mid 90's line of 'Unlimited' books alongside Spider-Man, X-Men, Fantastic Four & 2099 Unlimited.  Each book was published quarterly, was giant-sized and was published on better quality paper stock.

Cosmic Powers Unlimited was an anthology series exclusively featuring Marvel's Cosmic characters; each issue having a lead story then one or more shorter backups.  Each issue's lead story featured either the Silver Surfer solo or the Surfer with Quasar and Beta Ray Bill as the Star Masters.  Characters featured in backup features included: Jack of Hearts, Ganymede, Sundragon, Drax the Destroyer, Moondragon, Pip the Troll, Thanos, Captain Mar-Vell and Her / Kismet.

Cosmic Powers Unlimited ran for a mere 5 issues.
name: Cosmic Powers Unlimited

description:
Marvel Comics takes on this classic American tale adapted from L. Frank Baum. Writer Eric Shanower and artist Skottie Young have teamed up to produce a spectacularly appealing series great for all ages. In issue 1 of 8, Dorothy and Toto experience the tornado sweeping their house to the land of Oz. The house crushes one of the wicked witches. The good witch of the North tells Dorothy that she is also a witch, much to Dorothy's chagrin; like many children she believed all witches were evil and she didn't want to be one. By the end of issue 1, Dorothy finally meets her first companion, the Scarecrow. Together they continue on the yellow brick road to get to the center of the land to meet the powerful wizard called Oz.

Collected Editions

  • Oz Omnibus
  • Oz: The Wonderful Wizard of Oz
name: The Wonderful Wizard of Oz

description:
From acclaimed Doctor Who novelist David McIntee comes a new Ray Harryhausen Presents adventure! The quest to find the Golden Fleece is over, but now Jason and his band of Argonauts must embark on a new and more difficult journey-- the journey home! Pursued by a vengeful Aeetes, the Argonauts will brave many dangers, encounter old friends and new, and face enemies also both old and new. But when the gods play games, no one can avoid reaching the lands of the dead forever! This special edition has never before seen images and character designs from the series.
